{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Add deterministic public-exposure signals to the code-review security overlay (publicly-exposed-without-auth)\n\n## Context\nFollow-up to a278. Plan-review reasons over PROSE, so it cannot do true reachability analysis; the\ndeterministic \"is this publicly exposed?\" signals belong to the **code-review** gate, which sees the\nactual `*.tf` / docker-compose diff. This adds tfsec/Checkov-**aligned** detectors that flag a network\nservice exposed to untrusted networks — the code-level counterpart to a278's T10 plan-level\n`endpoint_access_contract`.\n\n## Design decisions (resolving the review BLOCK)\n- **Native opengrep rules, tfsec/Checkov-ALIGNED (not integrated).** There is no tfsec/Checkov\n  integration seam in the grounding layer (the `sarif` backend is hardwired to gitleaks). So the\n  detectors are authored as native opengrep rules under\n  `src/rebar/grounding/detectors/builtin/security_iac_public_exposure.yaml`, each citing the\n  equivalent tfsec / Checkov rule id in its message/metadata (e.g. tfsec `aws-vpc-no-public-ingress-sgr`,\n  Checkov `CKV_AWS_260`). opengrep runs via the `semgrep` fallback binary already on PATH.\n- **Deny-by-default EXPOSURE signal, NOT a deterministic auth-correlation.** A single opengrep rule\n  cannot reliably prove \"no authenticating gateway fronts this\" (the gateway/mesh/network-policy may\n  live outside the diff). So the detector fires on the deterministic EXPOSURE signal only and its\n  message states the deny-by-default obligation (\"public exposure — verify an authenticating gateway /\n  mTLS / network policy fronts this\"). Auth-absence is the reviewer's judgement, cued by the finding,\n  not a separate deterministic match.\n- **ADVISORY, not a hard block (new dedicated `exec: \"DET\"` criterion).** The detectors are filed under\n  a NEW criterion `public-exposure-without-auth` with its own detector id-prefix\n  (`rebar.builtin.iac.public-exposure.`), NOT under the fail-closed `high-critical-security` prefix.\n  Posture is `blocking_enabled: false` / `fail_mode: \"open\"`: a match is surfaced as an advisory\n  coverage finding, never an auto-BLOCK — so \"boundary controls outside the diff\" are weighed by the\n  reviewer, and FP-guarded cases are \"lower severity, not a hard block\", exactly as the AC requires.\n- **FP guards are pattern exclusions.** The rules match only unambiguous public exposure literals\n  (`0.0.0.0/0`, `::/0`, `associate_public_ip_address = true`, `internal = false` on an `aws_lb`, a\n  `0.0.0.0:` host-published compose port). Private-CIDR (`10.0.0.0/8`, `192.168.0.0/16`), loopback\n  (`127.0.0.1`), unix-socket, and `internal = true` do NOT match — so they are never flagged.\n- **engine_b applicability fix (mandatory).** `engine_b._LANG_EXTENSIONS` has no `terraform`/`yaml`\n  entry, so a detector declaring `languages: [terraform]` is skipped as `unsupported_lang`. Add\n  `terraform`/`hcl` → `.tf`/`.tfvars` and `yaml` → `.yml`/`.yaml` mappings.\n- **Data-driven wiring (story 7f0d).** Do NOT edit `code_review/detectors.py` (the consumer is\n  data-driven since 7f0d); the new criterion is picked up from its routing `detector` selector. The\n  new criterion's `applies_to` includes docker-compose globs (the `iac` glob list omits them).\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. A diff opens a security-group ingress `0.0.0.0/0` (or `::/0`) to a service port, gives an instance a\n   public IP, stands up an internet-facing LB, or publishes a container port on `0.0.0.0`.\n2. The current code-review security overlay does not deterministically flag that public exposure.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- **Expected:** a deterministic advisory finding on a publicly-reachable service in the diff, cueing the\n  reviewer to verify authentication/gateway.\n- **Actual:** no such deterministic signal exists in the code-review gate.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `src/rebar/grounding/detectors/builtin/security_iac_public_exposure.yaml` adds opengrep rules under\n      the `rebar.builtin.iac.public-exposure.` id-prefix (dimension `has_iac`) detecting, on the diff:\n      SG/firewall ingress open to `0.0.0.0/0` or `::/0`; `associate_public_ip_address = true`; an\n      internet-facing LB (`internal = false` on `aws_lb`); a non-loopback (`0.0.0.0:`) host-published\n      docker-compose port. Each rule cites its tfsec / Checkov analog.\n- [ ] Deny-by-default framing: each finding's message names the exposure and the obligation to verify an\n      authenticating gateway / mTLS / network policy (the auth-absence cue), without asserting a\n      deterministic auth-correlation the rule cannot prove.\n- [ ] FP guards (pattern exclusions): private-CIDR-sourced ingress, loopback/unix-socket binds, and\n      `internal = true` LBs do NOT match. Posture is ADVISORY (`blocking_enabled: false`,\n      `fail_mode: \"open\"`) — a match surfaces as a coverage finding, never an auto-BLOCK, so boundary\n      controls outside the diff are the reviewer's call.\n- [ ] `engine_b._LANG_EXTENSIONS` gains `terraform`/`hcl` → `.tf`/`.tfvars` and `yaml` → `.yml`/`.yaml`\n      so the new detectors are applicable; a new `public-exposure-without-auth` `exec: \"DET\"` entry in\n      `src/rebar/llm/code_review/criteria_routing.json` selects the id-prefix and globs `*.tf` /\n      `*.tfvars` / `docker-compose*.y*ml` / `**/compose*.y*ml` (compose globs the `iac` list omits).\n- [ ] Unit tests: (positive) the new detectors register on the opengrep backend and a real semgrep run\n      matches a `0.0.0.0/0` ingress + a public-IP + a public-LB + a `0.0.0.0:` compose bind; (negative) a\n      private-CIDR / loopback / `internal = true` fixture yields NO match; and `apply_failclosed` keeps\n      the verdict PASS (advisory, non-blocking) on a match for this criterion. `make lint` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782933465022193001,"uuid":"ffffd337-09fe-4802-ba0d-ea128adf7db0"}